from what i can see dolfie dreams are resin cast as well. They warn you of the usage of acetone. Which is an good indicator these are resin cast.
You can use acetone to clean up faces. But you need to wash them of with water immediatly after. Since the acetone makes the material go brittle and slimy. So if you have to clean up faces acetone is ok, just dont let it delve. Clean up the face and wash under water instantly after. Long time exposure to acetone will make your doll break. :^(

If your pre-amp has an out, it may have a "direct monitor" feature which would allow you to hear. Otherwise I think you would need to go into your OS sound settings and "Listen to this device" to make the sound come out of your speakers, or headphones.

Thin, purple-blue lips cover a razor-sharp beak of black bone with which they frequently tear each other to shreds in fights over clients. These creatures secrete an addicting fluid from their erect penises which prolongs life by slowing metabolism. Addicts of Mugwump fluid are known as Reptiles. A number of these flow over chairs with their flexible bones and black-pink flesh. A fan of green cartilage covered with hollow, erectile hairs through which the Reptiles absorb the fluid sprouts from behind each ear. The fans, which move from time to time touched by invisible currents, serve also some form of communication known only to reptiles.
The Sailor spotted his Reptile. He drifted over and ordered a green syrup. The Reptile had a little, round disk mouth of brown gristle, expressionless green eyes almost covered by a thin membrane of eyelid. The Sailor waited an hour before the creature picked up his presence.
"Any eggs for Fats?" he asked, his words stirring through the Reptile's fan hairs.
It took two hours for the Reptile to raise three pink transparent fingers covered with black fuzz.
Several Meat Eaters lay in vomit, too weak to move. (The Black Meat is like a tainted cheese, overpoweringly delicious and nauseating so that the eaters eat and vomit and eat again until they fall exhausted.)
A painted youth slithered in and seized one of the great black claws sending the sweet, sick smell curling through the café.

posts.com: Good morning. I’m Wilford Brimley, and I’d like to talk to you for a few minutes about diabetes. Actually about diabetes and how it has affected me in my life. I’ll start when I was first diagnosed: I was scared to death. I was experiencing symptoms that were strange and unfamiliar to me. For instance: I had an unquenchable thirst, my tongue felt like a horseshoe rasp, I was losing my vision, I was losing my energy, I was getting up every 15 or 20 minutes all through the night, so I wasn’t getting any rest and as result of all these things, I lost all my energy. And I was scared. A man doesn’t like to admit that he’s scared, but I truly was. I wasn’t afraid to die, I knew that was coming to all of us, but what I was afraid of was that I might have to live a long time feeling like I felt, and I really wasn’t interested in that. So finally, at the urging of my family, the ones who love me the most, I went to see a doctor, and he explained things to me in a language that I understood. And I think the most important thing he said to me was, “Wilford, if you wanna get better, I’m going to give you a few things to do. And the more attention you pay to these things, and the more diligent you are, the faster you’ll get better, and the better you’ll feel.” And ladies and gentlemen, that’s exactly the way it’s been.Through the years, the closer I paid attention to the instructions of my doctor, the better I feel. Now, I’m not perfect and I’ve slipped up, and I’ve eaten ice cream and apple pie and I’ve done things I shouldn’t do. But I wanna tell you, when I don’t eat apple and I don’t eat ice cream, and I eat the foods that I am supposed to eat and I do my exercises and I take my medicine and I do the procedures that I was instructed to do, I do feel better.I would encourage all of you to find a doctor that you trust and understand.

the girls silently leave their shoes at the door and walk inside shivering. you usher them to the bathroom and grab some casual shirts and shorts to let them wear.

at midnight, you decide to let the girls sleep. before you go, sandra asks to be hugged. you hug her.

If this is a serious thread, I would love to share my story. If not, just pretend this isn't here.

My life was literally saved by amphetamine (and ruined it because gov is dumb).
I live in a country where Ritalin is almost inaccessible, and amphetamine is illegal. I didn't knew back than I had ADHD, I just thought I'm a dumb and lazy person who always wants to run around.
In middle school a friend of mine got hooked on weed, so I tried it. Not really my type of drug, but it felt good. Then we got to try speed, and my life turned around. I cleaned my room, started a lot of friendships, in fact, I got my first gf. I graduated because of amphetamine. I got my first job because of amphetamine. I got a lots of things in my life because of that.
Then we got a drugtest at work. I failed ofc.
They found at least 100 grams of amphetamine at my house, so rehab wasn't an option for me (I ordered from DW, and always had to buy a LOT, but only did 50-100mg a day).
I was in prison for 2 years. Now I'm "clean", I lost all my friends, I lost my job, currently I work at a McDonalds where I fuck up everything on daily basis, I LOST EVERYTHING JUST BECAUSE I WANTED TO LIVE A FUCKING LIFE
Got diagnosis, got Strattera, but that shit isn't working for me, even though I'm on it for months now. I can't concentrate, I'm unable to sit on a chair for more than 5 minutes, and other stuff. They stole 2 years from me, they stole my only option to live a normal life, and fucked it up even more. They did "justice". Fuck them, I hope their kids have ADHD too.
You probably know by now which side I'm on.

The most tragic thing about this, that when I was in prison, most of us were there because of drugs, and I can say, all of us were harmless.
There were dealers too, but there were an old guy, I would never forget him, he got there because he grew weed. Fucking weed, really? Never sell it, just do it for fun. He grew it in his garden, and one his neighbors spit him in. He was more than 60 at the time. He could have been an alcoholic who beat his wife or some shit, but he didn't. He just smoked weed and chill'd.
There was a kid, he was just became 18 that year, he had anxious disorder with panic attacks. When his doc refused to give him more xannies, he went to illegal sources, and fucked it up instantly. Most of the time when he had an attack, we were the ones who calmed him down, because nobody did anything. We were just "drug addict freaks" to the guards and other people there. Nobody cared about us.
Welcome to the modern world, if you want to have fun, do work, or just get rid of your problems with the easiest method, you will get fucked hard, and they will ruin your life. It doesn't matter if you're in the States, or in a forgotten eastern EU country, you will get fucked hard. People will always point at you, like "Yeah, this guy was in prison, careful with him!" and they doesn't care what was the thing you were in for. They say you will always be an addict, try to force you on therapists, and when the therapist says you're healthy, and actually have ADHD, people will still don't care.
The first thing we need to do is get the message to all people. We're not addicts, because if you have an addiction, you will get help and want to get rid of it. We're not freaks, we're just the same people as anyone. We're not fucked up, and DEFINITELY NOT criminals. We just do things differently. We just made different choices, and that's all. If non-users understand us, they will be on our side. Sorry for long comments.
